Search across my Gmail, Slack, Jira, and Google Calendar for the past 2 weeks and the next 2 weeks. Act as my Chief of Staff and give me a diagnostic view of every initiative I'm currently touching. Cut through the noise and give me the high-level picture.

For each initiative:
• Initiative Name — your best synthesized label
• What It Is — one sentence, what is this actually about
• My Role — am I driving it, contributing to it, or just being pulled in?
• Current Status — on track, stalled, or needs attention? Tag source with SOURCE ATTRIBUTION format.
• Am I the Blocker? — explicitly answer yes or no. If yes, what specific action from me would unblock it?
• What's Next — the single most important thing that needs to happen in the next 7 days, and whether that's on me or someone else
• Horizon — this-week, this-month, or longer-term

Sort by urgency. Flag anything drifting without clear ownership.

After listing all initiatives, give me:

STATE OF THE BOARD — one paragraph, your honest read on where I'm spread too thin, what deserves more focus than it's getting, and what I should stop letting pull my attention. Apply OVERLOAD CALIBRATION: distinguish high-leverage stretch from capacity drain.

WHERE I'M ACTUALLY BLOCKING — a separate, prominent callout of the 1-3 places where my inaction is creating the most downstream cost right now. Name the person waiting, how long they've been waiting, and what it would take to unblock them.
